AppMan Manifest for TEAM ROM

This will also function as a template for all future ROM's

First Commit

Pvy.

Rom XML Format
	<roms>
		<rom>
			<rom_name>T.E.A.M.</rom_name>
			
			    **rom name also the detected name 
	    		**MUST BE IN BUILD PROP display ID can 
	    		**have more info there but this string 
	    		**must be part of it. eg,
	    			**Build id "T.E.A.M. v5 22/11/11"
	    			**rom name "T.E.A.M."
	    		**notice that the rom name is IN the build id :)
	    		
			<phone>x10</phone> 
			
				**phone model type
				
			<dev>pvyParts and iridaki</dev>
			 
				**dev credits
				
			<github_name>pvyParts</github_name> 
			
				**github user name for manifest
				
			<apps>true</apps> 
			
				**app addons boolean
				
			<tweaks>ture</tweaks> 
			
				**optional tweaks boolean
				
			<mods>true</mods> 
			
				**rom optional mods boolean
				
			<updates>true</updates> 
			
				**rom update zips boolean
				
			<themes>true</themes>
			 
				**themes boolean
				
			<kernels>true</kernels> 
			
				**supports kernels boolean
				
		</rom>
	</roms>
	 
All Item Format
	<apps>	    
		<app>	    
			<name>Stock Timescape</name>
			
			**Name of addon / app
			
			<moddate>01-01-2012</moddate>
			
			**Date of addition / update / change
			**Date format
			**"dd-MM-yyyy"
			**"-" delimiter!!!! IMPORTANT TO USE THIS
			
			<credits>pvyParts</credits>
			
			<url>http://google.com</url>
			
			**link to the apps homepage /a forum post / what ever
			
			<version>V123456</version>
			
			**Version of the mod / update / app ect ect
			
			<description>blah blah blah some app that does blah blah</description>
			
			**yeah that dont need explination
			
			<files>
				<file filename="app1.apk" location="system/app/" perms="0644" appurl="http://some.web.page/files/app1.apk" md5="12345678910111213141516171819202" />
				<file filename="app2.apk" location="system/app/" perms="0644" appurl="http://some.web.page/files/app2.apk" md5="12345678910111213141516171819202" />

				**List of files
				**Mulptiple files possible
				**each file has these params
					
					**filename= the name of the file eg "AppMan.apk" Case Sensitive must incluude extension if it has one.
					
					**location= the install location of the file eg "system/app/" thats self explanitory
					
					**perms= the perms that the file needs eg "0644" (most system apps ect)
					
					**appurl= the location of the file for it to be downloaded from. must be a direct link file service. eg "http://android.magnificentblog.com/files/AppMan.apk"
					
					**md5= the md5 hash of the file for download checks - if no md5 suplied the app wont install
					
			</files>
		</app>
	</apps>